          "2": {
            "include_page": true,
            "images": {
              "page-002.jpg": {
                "type": "extração-latex",
                "include": true,
                "description": "11\n\nFIB: $\\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nFIB(0) = 0 \\\\\nFIB(1) = 1 \\\\\nFIB(m) = FIB(m-2) + FIB(m-1), & \\text{se } m \\geq 2\n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\ne) $DIV: \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$  \nPRÉ: $y > 0$  \nPÓS: $DIV(x, y) = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{x}{y} \\right\\rfloor$\n\n$DIV(x, y) = DIVAUX(x, y, 0)$\n\n$DIVAUX: \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$  \nPRÉ: $y > 0$  \nPÓS: $DIVAUX(x, y, c) = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{x}{y} \\right\\rfloor + c$\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nDIVAUX(x, y, c) = c, & \\text{se } x < y \\\\\nDIVAUX(x, y, c) = DIVAUX(x - y, y, c + 1), & \\text{se } x \\geq y\n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\nou\n\n$DIV: \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$  \nPRÉ: $y > 0$  \nPÓS: $DIV(x, y) = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{x}{y} \\right\\rfloor$\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nDIV(x, y) = 0, & \\text{se } x < y \\\\\nDIV(x, y) = 1 + DIV(x - y, y), & \\text{se } x \\geq y\n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\n2) $MULT: \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$  \nPRÉ: T  \nPÓS: $MULT(x, y) = x \\times y$\n\nPUCRS",
                "described_at": "2026-04-17T21:18:53"
              }
            }
          },
          "3": {
            "include_page": true,
            "images": {
              "page-003.jpg": {
                "type": "extração-latex",
                "include": true,
                "description": "11\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nMULT(x, y) = 0, & \\text{se } x = 0 \\\\\nMULT(x, y) = MULT\\left(\\frac{x}{2}, 2 \\times y\\right), & \\text{se } x \\text{ é par} \\\\\nMULT(x, y) = MULT\\left(\\frac{x-1}{2}, 2 \\times y\\right) + y, & \\text{se } x \\text{ é ímpar}\n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\nou\n\n$$MULT(x, y) = MULTAUX(x, y, 0)$$\n\nMULTAUX: $\\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\rightarrow \\mathbb{N}$\n\nPRE: T\n\nPOS: $MULTAUX(a, y, a) = a \\times y + a$\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nMULTAUX(x, y, a) = a, & \\text{se } x = 0 \\\\\nMULTAUX(x, y, a) = MULTAUX\\left(\\frac{x}{2}, 2 \\times y, a\\right), & \\text{se } x \\text{ é par} \\\\\nMULTAUX(x, y, a) = MULTAUX\\left(\\frac{x-1}{2}, 2 \\times y, a + y\\right), & \\text{se } x \\text{ é ímpar}\n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\n3 FAT: $\\mathbb{N} \\rightarrow \\mathbb{N}$\n\nPRE: T\n\nPOS: $FAT(x) = x!$\n\n$FAT(x) = FATAUX(x, 1)$\n\nFATAUX: $\\mathbb{N} \\times \\mathbb{N} \\rightarrow \\mathbb{N}$\n\nPRE: T\n\nPOS: $FATAUX(a, a) = x \\times a$\n\n$$\n\\begin{cases}\nFATAUX(0, a) = a, & \\text{se } x = 0 \\\\\nFATAUX(x+1, a) = FATAUX(x, a \\times (x+1)), & \n\\end{cases}\n$$\n\nPUCRS",
                "described_at": "2026-04-17T21:21:14"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
